\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\b\f3 Brainstorming\par
{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}Prototype \b0\f0\par
\pard\li720 A prototype is a playable early version of the game or part of the game constructed\par
by the designer to assist in understanding and enhancing the player experience.\par
It may be done with software (\ldblquote digital prototype\rdblquote ) or with physical materials as\par
a tabletop game (\ldblquote physical prototype\rdblquote  or \ldblquote paper prototype\rdblquote )\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\b\f3 Balance\par
\pard\li720\b0\f0 When play is balanced, it provides a consistent challenge\par
for its target audience\b\f3\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720 Mechanics\par
\pard\b0\f0\tab The rules of a game\tab\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\b\f3 Dynamics\par
\pard\li720\b0\f0 In \i\f1 Chess\i0\f0 , the moves of the pieces are mechanics,\par
but \ldblquote book openings\rdblquote  (well-known sequences of moves at the start of the game) are dynamics.\b\f3\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720 System\par
\pard\li720\b0\f0 A collection of game mechanics that is responsible for producing a given\par
outcome within a larger game such as character creation, combat, or casting spells\b\f3\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720 Avatar\par
{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}Playtesting\par
\pard\li720\b0\f0 The systematic testing of gameplay, systems, balance, and interface to find\par
all the errors, inconsistencies, or issues and report them to the design team.\b\f3\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720 Concept Doc\b0\f0\par
\pard\li720 A one- to three-page document that provides a high-level overview of a\par
proposed game.\b\f3\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720 Proposal\b0\f0\par
\pard\li720\b\f3  \b0\f0 A five- to 20-page document that provides a more in-depth view of the potential\par
game than a concept document. Like a concept document, it typically contains an introductory paragraph, a demographic breakdown, a gameplay summary, a feature list, and a feature-list breakout.\b\f3\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720 Pitch\par
{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}Design Document\b0\f0\par
\pard\li720\b\f3  \b0\f0 A \ldblquote living\rdblquote  document that is continuously undergoing revision, it contains the entire design vision for the game. It may be in a document file or in a wiki.\par
Some teams use Agile development, which requires no design document at all. More\par
information on Agile can be found at AgileManifesto.org. Game design documents\par
(GDDs) are usually separate from the technical design document (TDD) for programmers\par
and the art style guide for the art team\b\f3\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720 Alpha: \b0\f0\par
\pard\li720 The milestone at which all systems have been implemented and all code is theoretically\par
complete. It is usually full of bugs, however, and not terribly balanced. Some\par
companies also require that all content\emdash art, sound, and narrative\emdash be implemented\par
for alpha, too. Therefore, alpha is content- and code-complete.\b\f3\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720 Beta\b0\f0\par
\pard\b\f3  \tab\b0\f0 The milestone at which all systems and content are in the game. It is significantly\par
\pard\li720 more stable than the alpha version, and many of the big bug and balancing issues have\par
been addressed.\b\f3\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720 Gold\par
\pard\tab\b0\f0 The final version of the game that is then released.\b\f3\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720 Game Jam\b0\f0\par
\pard\li720\b\f3  \b0\f0 A timed period during which a group of individuals attempts to create a\par
complete game while working around the clock. These events are usually 1\endash 3 days in\par
duration.\b\f3\par
