\b0\f0\ldblquote Game mechanic\rdblquote  is another term for what others might commonly call a \ldblquote rule.\rdblquote\par
If you do X, then Y happens. If X is true, then you can do Y.\par
A mechanic makes every game designer ask, \ldblquote What can I make with this?\rdblquote  A mechanic is all about possibility.\par
\par
common classes of mechanics that are usually found in games:\par
\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\b\f3 Setup. \b0\f0\par
\pard\b\f3\tab\b0\f0 There must always be at least one rule that describes how the game begins.\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\b\f3 Victory conditions. \b0\f0\par
\pard\b\f3\tab\b0\f0 There must always be at least one rule that describes how the game\par
\tab is won. Some games, like open-ended role-playing games (RPGs), have no victory \tab condition. As a result, some designers do not consider them games. Others consider the\par
\tab achievement of a specific goal a victory as they race off to the next goal.\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\b\f3 Progression of play. \b0\f0\par
\pard\b\f3\tab\b0\f0 Who goes first, and how (see Figure 2.4)? Is the game turn based\par
\pard\li720 or real time? For turn-based games, does the game start with one player and then proceed\par
clockwise, or do players bid resources in an auction for the right to go first each\par
round, or is there some other method? For real-time games, when two players try to do\par
something at the same time, how is that resolved?\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\b\f3 Player actions. \b0\f0\par
\pard\li720 Sometimes referred to as \ldblquote verbs,\rdblquote  some of the most important mechanics\par
describe what players can do and what effect those actions have on the game state.\par
\pard{\pntext\f6\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf6\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\b\f3 Definition of game view(s).\b0\f0\par
\pard\li720 Mechanics define exactly what information each player\par
knows at any given time. Note that some mechanics may change the view, such as partially lifting fog of war in an RTS under certain conditions.\par
\pard\b\f3\par
